{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Unit->Integration: failure can occur at the handoff between vision-classification result and moderation-state transition (hold vs publish). Integration->System: this behavior depends on the real model-serving boundary (real model endpoint/runtime behavior), not just in-process logic. System->Agentic: correctness depends on real vision-model output quality for explicit-content detection; stubbed outputs would miss true misclassification failures. Rejected Workflow: behavior is a single agentic classification plus decision, not multiple agentic steps in sequence.","test_description":"Run end-to-end moderation for real explicit-image samples using the production vision model path, then assert each submission is stored as held-for-review and never reaches publish state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Unit->Integration: failure appears at classifier-output to moderation-decision handoff. Integration->System: test must use the real text-model serving path to exercise real request/response behavior, not only a fake classifier. System->Agentic: this is fundamentally about model robustness to obfuscation; deterministic stubs would always pass and hide true detection failures. Rejected Workflow: only one agentic classification behavior is under test, not a multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Submit a corpus of obfuscated hate-speech text variants through the real text moderation path and assert each is flagged/held across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit->Integration: failure is at module handoff when two checker outcomes are combined into one publish/hold/drop decision and persisted/dispatched. Integration-brake: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess is required by behavior text; (b) no dependence on AI output quality because behavior says the post already passes both checks; (c) no multi-agentic chain requirement. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow based on explicit text 'passes both content checks' and focus on routing outcome.","test_description":"Wire moderation service with in-process fakes for image/text checkers returning PASS, then assert the orchestrator publishes exactly once and does not create hold records or drop the post.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Unit->Integration: latency budget is consumed across multiple modules in one pipeline. Integration->System: real timing failures depend on external/runtime effects (real model call latency, network jitter, queueing, process scheduling) that in-process mocks hide. Rejected Agentic: pass/fail criterion is elapsed time, not model output quality/non-deterministic correctness. Rejected Workflow: this is one pipeline execution, not multiple agentic stages requiring separate quality judgments.","test_description":"Execute the real moderation service under representative load with real infrastructure paths, measure submit-to-final-decision latency, and assert p95/p99 (or strict per-item bound per spec) is <= 5 seconds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"System is required specifically for realistic latency behavior; model semantic quality is not the assertion target.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit->Integration: failure occurs at interface handoff between vision-check failure signal and moderation fallback path (enqueue retry vs approve). Integration-brake: (a) behavior text requires handling 'unavailable' state, which can be reproduced with an in-process fake client error contract; no explicit OS/network primitive is required. (b) correctness does not depend on AI output quality. (c) no multi-agentic sequence. Rejected System because the behavior does not require validating specific real network failure modes, only correct fallback decisioning.","test_description":"Use a fake vision-client module that returns service-unavailable errors and verify the moderation orchestrator enqueues retry jobs and never marks the post approved/published.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"If future acceptance criteria specify exact timeout/error-code mapping from real HTTP, this should be upgraded to System.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.27,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Unit->Integration: consistency failure can appear where repeated classification outputs interact with decision/caching logic. Integration->System: repeated submissions must traverse the real model-serving/runtime path to expose real variance sources hidden by fakes. System->Agentic: behavior explicitly depends on borderline-image model behavior consistency/non-determinism across runs; stubbed deterministic outputs would mask the failure. Rejected Workflow: repeated submissions are repetitions of one agentic decision pattern, not a multi-agentic step pipeline.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image multiple times within the target window through the real moderation path and assert decision consistency rate meets policy (or deterministic consistency if required) while confirming hold/publish outcomes are stable.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.21,"Agentic":0.66,"Workflow":0.04}}]}
